column1: # description: data for testing correlation matrix routine including correlation of missingness

column2: description: some X values centered on zero
description: a copy of X to get correlation coefficient with X of +1 exactly
description: -1* X to get correlation coefficient with X of -1 exactly
description: X value if X is integer; otherwise missing. Hoping for -1 correlation of missingness with Only_Fractional_X
description: X value if X is fractional (noninteger); otherwise missing. Hoping for -1 correlation of missingness with Only_Integer_X
description: yes_Integer or blank. Hoping for +1 correlation of missingness with Only_Integer_X; and -1 correlation of missingness with Only_Fractional_X
description: yes_Prime or not_Prime or missing
description: square root of X; provides a nontrivial correlation coefficient with X and +1 correlation of missingness with Is_NonNegative
description: if X is negative then give NaN rather than blank
description: the square of X; provides zero correlation with X since X is symmetric across zero
description: cube root of X. Provides nontrivial correlation with X whether X is NonNegative or negative.
description: Just the arbitrarily chosen number 12345 regardless of X. Provides a NaN correlation with X.

description: X times 1e20 or 10^20; provides +1 correlation with X unless there are roundoff problems; which seem likely. Chose 1e20 since some calculations might use Avogadro's Number 6.022e23 but 1e20 is a nicer number. Single precision floating point max is about 1e38.

description: X times 1e100 or 10^100; provides +1 correlation with X unless there are roundoff problems; which seem likely. Chose 1e100 since it's above single float max but below double float max which is about 1e308
